President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Alaska due to flooding from May 8 to May 11, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The Copper River Regional Educational Attendance Area (REAA), Iditarod REAA, and Kuspuk REAA are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, federal funding is available statewide for hazard mitigation measures. Yolanda J. Jackson has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.